  "text": "Our results are in agreement with these findings in both years studied. A study about socio-economic status, obesity, and lifestyle also concluded that subjects from lower socio-economic status had greater measures of obesity despite being more physically active at work [CITATION_1] . To have an unskilled manual job is associated with the probability of becoming obese, and this fact is exacerbated by a poor financial situation, as is an economic crisis. This fact is supported by social class differences found in our results and by the significant difference obtained between the years 2006 and 2012. This gap has widened by economic crisis. At the same time, odds between SHEI and social class also shows a high risk to have a poor diet in the population with unskilled manual job, and this risk increased in 2012.",
